      </label>
      <label style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:.6rem;font-size:.97rem;color:#1a1a18;font-weight:600;cursor:default;">
        <input type="checkbox" style="width:1.1rem;height:1.1rem;accent-color:#c8500a;flex-shrink:0;" /> Dry seasoned wood ready
      </label>
      <label style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:.6rem;font-size:.97rem;color:#1a1a18;font-weight:600;cursor:default;">
        <input type="checkbox" style="width:1.1rem;height:1.1rem;accent-color:#c8500a;flex-shrink:0;" /> Flue primed if cold or first fire of season
      </label>
      <label style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:.6rem;font-size:.97rem;color:#1a1a18;font-weight:600;cursor:default;">
        <input type="checkbox" style="width:1.1rem;height:1.1rem;accent-color:#c8500a;flex-shrink:0;" /> Top-down build with fire starters on top
      </label>
      <label style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:.6rem;font-size:.97rem;color:#1a1a18;font-weight:600;cursor:default;">
        <input type="checkbox" style="width:1.1rem;height:1.1rem;accent-color:#c8500a;flex-shrink:0;" /> Wait for kindling to burn fully before adding logs
      </label>
      <label style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:.6rem;font-size:.97rem;color:#1a1a18;font-weight:600;cursor:default;">
        <input type="checkbox" style="width:1.1rem;height:1.1rem;accent-color:#c8500a;flex-shrink:0;" /> Adjust air controls down once fire established
      </label>
    </div>
  </div>

  <p>If smoke comes back in: check damper, prime flue, crack a window to test for negative pressure. If still not drawing — the flue needs a clean.</p>

